Performers from opera troupes nationwide has kicked off their two-month performances in Beijing, presenting a diversity of traditional Chinese operas.Hosted by the Publicity Department of the Communist Party of China Central Committee and the Ministry of Culture and Tourism, the event will provide audiences with a feast of Chinese operas including Pingju Opera, Qinqiang Opera and Chao Opera, all of which are different opera types with local distinctions.The performances, which will last until mid-August, offer tickets at low prices, so that more people can enjoy the country's intangible culture heritage, said the organizers.Moreover, a seminar on artistic creation by primary-level opera troupes will be held during the event. 
